Add django_nose to apps only when testing

In base.py, only add django_nose to INSTALLED_APPS if 'test' is
in sys.argv, which seems like the simplest way to only load it
when running a test. (We don't install django_nose in production
anymore, so need it not to be in INSTALLED_APPS otherwise.)

Merge pull request #64 from dpoirier/bug-852965-basket-auth

Bug 852965 - add secure API to look up users

Bug 852965 - add secure API to look up users

* New lookup-user API
* Requires SSL
* Can look up by token or by email.
* Looking up by email requires a shared secret "API key" to be included.
* Doc added to README.rst
* Tests added

Notes:

* This just adds a new API and does not change the behavior of any existing APIs, so should be safe to deploy without breaking anybody.
* If production basket is behind a proxy or load balancer, the check for SSL might not work right without some settings changes (see https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.5/ref/settings/#std:setting-SECURE_PROXY_SSL_HEADER)

Bug 863033: Three basket fixes

1) When language, country, or format is not yet set in ET, the database
   there will have NULL and ET will return None. Fix that to '' so
   we can use it later without worrying about whether it's None.
2) Only set CREATED_DATE_ in ET when we create a new user in ET, not
   when we create a new user in Basket.
3) When the user changes languages and subscribes to things at the same
   time, use the new language they chose when sending their welcome
   messages.

Bug 884598: Handle welcome languages correctly

We should only send a welcome message in a language
that its newsletter supports. Otherwise, use English.

Bug 863066: Fix subscription data returned

There was a bug in how we translated from what Exact Target gives us
to our preferred internal representation of what newsletters the user
is subscribed to. The symptom was that when a user confirmed, we
thought they hadn't subscribed to anything and so didn't send any
welcome messages.

Merge pull request #50 from dpoirier/bug-863066-check-error-in-confirm-task

In confirm_user task, add a check that we got a user_data object,
but it showed an error. Log the error and raise the right exception
so our task framework will retry.

Also add a few tests for this task, which didn't appear to have any
tests previously.

Bug 865058: Add order field to newsletters

Add an `order` field to newsletters. Bedrock already has code on the
newsletter preference center page so that if the newsletters include
an `order` field, they'll be sorted by that for display, instead of
by the title.

Also update the admin config to make it easier to work with the order
fields, by making them editable right in the display list.  Add a
few other fields to that for good measure.

Merge pull request #45 from dpoirier/bug-overwriting-user-format-preference

Only change user format preference on request

If an update_user call didn't specify a preference for email format
(T or H), Basket was defaulting to 'H', then setting that in ET
even if the user had previously selected 'T'.

Instead, don't send ET a format if the API call didn't specify one.
We still use the user's previous preference, if any, for sending
their welcome messages, or else HTML.
